h4. Current behaviour

- Let's say we have project "A" and project "B";
- One group have the "Browse project" permission only in project "A", but not in project "B";
- Users will be able to see issues from project A but not from project B;
- If you link an issue from project A in an issue from project A, the user will be able to see the "linked issues" just fine;
- If you link an issue from project B in an issue from project A, users won't see the "linked issue";

h4. Expected

For some companies, being aware that an issue from an specific project (even if you don't have the permission to view it) relates to another issue would be really important.

