I am trying to show an" Issue creation form" in an iFrame, by reusing some of the the Jira JS code.

This works in Jira 4.x and Jira 5.0. But things just do not show correctly in Jira 5.1 and 5.2.

It looks like this is a problem with the cross-domain politic, an iFrame cannot execute JS if the parent window comes from a different domain than the one shown in the iFrame.

If we edit the JIRA code, (<JIRAInstallDir>\atlassian-jira\includes\jquery\plugins\scrollIntoView\scrollIntoView.js and scrollIntoView-min.js), we can get things working.

What to edit:
The files are scollIntoView.js & scrollIntoView-min.js, we want to replace this line:

	var jQuery = window.top.jQuery || window.jQuery;

with:

	var jQuery;
	try {
		jQuery = window.top.jQuery || window.jQuery;
	} catch (e) {
		jQuery = window.jQuery;
	}
	

Steps:
1. I have made the modification in <JIRAInstallDir>\atlassian-jira\includes\jquery\plugins\scrollIntoView\scrollIntoView.js and scrollIntoView-min.js (Modify both, if the "-min.js" is not present Jira takes the scrollIntoView.js first, but if both are present, it looks like Jira uses the "-min.js" one, )
2. Restarted the server
3. I tried in IE 9.0.8 (WinSer 2008) , FF 19.0.2 (Win 7) and Chrome 25.0.1364 (Win 7)
4. All the browsers work fine with the iFrame.

This tickek is a request to provide a fix for the JS code, in case the code is running in an iFrame, would you add the code that is shown above to get the correct value in the code please?

